A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO TRADE.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION I. Chapter 201, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
3 and to read as follows:
4 ”§201- Hawaii-Ireland trade commission; established;
5 membership; duties. (a) There is established within the
6 department, for administrative purposes only, the Hawaii-Ireland
7 trade commission. The commission shall consist of five members
8 who shall be appointed as follows:
9 (1) Three members to be appointed by the governor without
10 regard to section 26-34;
11 (2) One member to be appointed by the speaker of the house
12 of representatives; and
13 (3) One member to be appointed by the president of the
14 senate.
15 Each member shall be appointed for a four-year term;
16 provided that each member shall hold office until reappointed by
17 the member's respective appointing authority at the end of the
2026-3510 HB1391 CD2 HMSO
