1 member's term or until the member's successor is appointed. Any
2 vacancy shall be filled by the respective appointing authority.
3 All initial appointments shall be made no later than
4 October 1, 2026.
5 (b) The members of the commission shall elect a
6 chairperson and vice chairperson from among themselves.
7 (c) Any action taken by the commission shall be approved
8 by a simple majority of its members. A majority of the members
9 of the commission shall constitute a quorum to do business.
10 (d) Each member of the commission shall have:
11 (1) Knowledge of^ or current or past involvement in,
12 organizations that promote Irish affairs; or
13 (2) An interest in the well-being of trade relations
14 between Hawaii and Ireland.
15 (e) The commission shall:
16 (1) Advance bilateral trade and investment between Hawaii
17 and Ireland;
18 (2) Initiate joint action on policy issues of mutual
19 interest to Hawaii and Ireland;
20 (3) Promote business and academic exchanges between Hawaii
21 and Ireland;
