1 (4) Encourage mutual economic support between Hawaii and
2 Ireland;
3 (5) Encourage mutual investment in the infrastructure of
4 Hawaii and Ireland; and
5 (6) Address any other issues as determined by the
6 commission.
7 (f) Beginning with the regular session of 2028^ no later
8 than twenty days before the convening of each regular session,
9 the commission shall submit to the legislature and governor a
10 report of its work, during the previous year.
11 (g) The commission may adopt rules pursuant to chapter 91
12 to implement this section.
13 (h) As used in this section, "commission" means the
14 Hawaii-Ireland trade commission."
15 SECTION 2. New statutory material is underscored.
16 SECTION 3. This Act shall take effect upon its approval
17 and shall be repealed on June 30, 2031.
